17 2. The person had no criminal violations during the term of
18 probation;
19 3. The person has no pending revocation hearings; and
20 4. The district attorney does not object on behalf of the state
21 or the victim or victims of the offense. Any such objection shall
22 be made in writing, specify on behalf of whom the objection is made,
23 and include the specific reason or reasons for the objection.
